node.text:
We are proud to give you a first look at our partnership with SUGi, an organization committed to the reforestation of urban areas. Initially, we have been supporting four mini-forest projects in Australia, Cameroon and the USA. SUGi’s global network of forest makers, called Rewilders, create ultra-dense, biodiverse forests of native species only using a proven Japanese technique called the Miyawaki method. 
Discover more about the Rewilding Generation by clicking the link in bio.

We are proud to launch an innovative, sustainable watch box created entirely from upcycled plastic bottles. With the new box, Breitling underscores the brand’s commitment to reducing its environmental impact with fewer materials and a reduction of transport-related CO2 emissions. 

This new sustainable packaging concept has been awarded the Efficient Solution Label, delivered by the @SolarImpulse Foundation. 

The classic Breitling watch box will still be available to customers who request it. They will be encouraged to offset the environmental impact of their choice by making a voluntary contribution to our partner @sugiproject .

node.text:
A distinctive celebration of design and freedom, the new Breitling Top Time Classic Cars Squad pays homage to classic sports cars from the 1960s with a trio of racing chronographs. Drawing inspiration from the Chevrolet Corvette, Ford Mustang and Shelby Cobra, the timepieces are a nod to the original 1960s Breitling Top Time models, which were designed for « young and active professionals ». 

Discover the new collection via the link in bio
.
